oved availability and use of port recep- tion facilities for waste from commercial shipping, fishing vessels, recreational craft, aquaculture and offshore activities o general waste policy and regulatory frame- work focusing on the prevention of litter 39 https://www.health.belgium.be/en/marine-strategy-framework- directive 40 https://www.health.belgium.be/fr/programme-de-mesures- dcsmm-2016 o focus on plastics and circular economy in order to close the loop of materials o encourage research on the impact of mi- croplastics on human health o waste from beach tourism: awareness rais- ing to avoid littering and supporting volun- tary beach clean-ups o the collection of floating litter in waterways and ports: installing litter traps and assess- ing optimal clean-up technology o investigate the possibilities of improving sewage treatment plants to capture mi- croplastics o education: introduce the issue of marine lit- ter in school programs o communication campaigns (e.g. beach tourism, the link of land-based litter with marine litter, the possible impact of mi- croplastics on the human food chain, im- pact of the fishing industry, etc.)", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "a538f28a-566b-4b8d-8df4-67db3ad24f05": {"__data__": {"id_": "a538f28a-566b-4b8d-8df4-67db3ad24f05", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/national-marine-plastic-litter-policies-eu-member-states", "Author": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Publisher": "International Union for Conservation of Nature", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "National marine plastic litter policies in EU Member States", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.iucn.org/resources/grey-literature/national-m